==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Breasted
<hw>Breast"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a breast; -- used in
composition with qualifying words, in either a literal or a metaphorical
sense; <as>as, a single-<ex>breasted</ex> coat</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The close minister is buttoned up, and the brave officer
open-<qex>breasted</qex>, on these occasions.</q>
<rj><qau>Spectator.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Breastfast</ent>⟦br⟧
